  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nA scope like `echo:name` (typical format in Auth0 and other providers, ex, `read:profile` etc) is converted to `StringPermission` as an `echo:name` name, no actions. \r\nBut `@PermissionsAllowed(\"echo:name\")` produces `StringPermission` with its name set to `echo` and its action set to `name`.\r\nScope value like `echo:name` should be split by `:` and initialize `new StringPermission(\"echo\", \"name\")`.\r\n\r\nMinor problem, I can workaround with creating a custom `echo.name` scope for now\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
